WEBVTT

00:55.000 --> 00:55.734
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

00:55.734 --> 00:56.535
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

00:56.535 --> 00:57.269
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

00:57.269 --> 00:58.137
(for filming child actors and animals.)

01:59.932 --> 02:00.732
I don't need anything else.

02:00.732 --> 02:02.100
Just tell me
whether you killed my mom and dad.

02:02.100 --> 02:02.968
Myo Jin!

02:02.968 --> 02:03.869
Do you miss your parents?

02:03.869 --> 02:04.903
Do you need to see blood
before you'll be satisfied?

02:04.903 --> 02:06.071
If you want revenge,

02:06.572 --> 02:07.873
get your head on straight first.

02:07.873 --> 02:10.042
You have a secret too.

02:10.242 --> 02:11.877
I'm sorry. I was selfish.

02:12.478 --> 02:13.745
Your revenge...

02:13.745 --> 02:14.880
No matter what it takes,
get your memories back.

02:14.880 --> 02:15.914
The things I said to you,

02:15.914 --> 02:17.316
no matter how terrible the accident was,

02:17.316 --> 02:19.318
they're not something you can just forget.

02:38.270 --> 02:41.240
(Kidnapping)

03:22.714 --> 03:24.450
Unbelievable.

03:24.917 --> 03:26.051
Hey, hand me that.

03:28.720 --> 03:30.322
This stuff works instantly.

03:31.223 --> 03:32.958
Young Gu, buy this by the box.

03:32.958 --> 03:33.959
Yes, boss.

03:39.631 --> 03:40.766
You can't reach her?

03:41.333 --> 03:42.334
What are you saying?

03:42.334 --> 03:44.837
This is strange.
She's usually home by now.

03:45.070 --> 03:46.438
Since when has her phone been off?

03:47.206 --> 03:48.474
Well, that's...

03:49.842 --> 03:51.510
So you haven't even tried
calling her until now?

03:52.010 --> 03:53.545
Not until I called you?

03:53.545 --> 03:55.080
I'll call her right now.

03:55.280 --> 03:56.715
You're supposed to be
looking after Myo Jin.

03:56.715 --> 03:59.051
Where the hell has your head been?

03:59.718 --> 04:02.287
A person is missing,
and you don't know anything?

04:02.287 --> 04:04.056
This has never happened
to me before either.

04:04.456 --> 04:07.526
Then from now on, make her report
where she is and what she's doing.

04:07.526 --> 04:10.129
She goes wherever she wants
and doesn't answer my calls either.

04:10.129 --> 04:11.864
Why are you only blaming me?

04:11.864 --> 04:14.199
But today isn't a hospital day.

04:14.933 --> 04:17.002
So if she went out anyway,
you should've followed her,

04:17.002 --> 04:18.670
or at least known where she was going.

04:18.670 --> 04:19.505
And if not that,

04:20.038 --> 04:21.607
you should've set a time
for her to come home.

04:21.974 --> 04:23.575
Fine. I get it.

04:23.809 --> 04:26.545
I'll go out right now
and look around town.

04:26.545 --> 04:27.446
Happy?

04:46.465 --> 04:48.033
This is so simple.

04:48.033 --> 04:49.301
What has she been doing until now?

04:49.601 --> 04:50.936
I guess her housekeeper days are over,

04:51.937 --> 04:53.939
because Ryu Jun Ho's going to fire her.

05:02.281 --> 05:03.515
Boss.

05:03.916 --> 05:05.117
That guy over there...

05:05.684 --> 05:07.252
What? Is that the bastard from earlier?

05:10.155 --> 05:11.056
What's that?

05:11.757 --> 05:12.624
Hey, Young Gu.

05:13.459 --> 05:14.960
What's that bastard holding in his hand?

05:15.494 --> 05:16.428
Boss.

05:17.062 --> 05:18.630
It's a hammer.

05:25.938 --> 05:27.806
- What?
- Mr. An, long time no see.

05:27.806 --> 05:28.674
Why are you here?

05:29.508 --> 05:30.409
What?

05:34.012 --> 05:35.080
Are you the boss?

05:35.814 --> 05:37.182
Damn it. Young Gu, go!

06:52.224 --> 06:54.059
Like you said, I didn't kill him.

06:56.562 --> 06:57.896
There's a woman passed out in the car.

06:57.896 --> 06:58.764
What should I do?

07:00.332 --> 07:01.333
Did you do that?

07:02.234 --> 07:04.536
No, boss.
She was like that from the start.

07:06.271 --> 07:07.940
You want to date someone, don't you?

07:09.208 --> 07:11.243
No, sir. She's not my type.

07:12.377 --> 07:13.545
If you've got nothing to do,

07:14.279 --> 07:16.582
load this up, you punk.

07:18.550 --> 07:19.518
Yes, boss.

07:26.725 --> 07:29.528
(Joan Partners Architecture Office)

07:47.613 --> 07:50.149
What brings you here, ma'am?

07:50.149 --> 07:51.049
The CEO.

08:00.292 --> 08:01.093
Sir.

08:01.326 --> 08:02.394
You have a visitor.

08:06.031 --> 08:07.966
What did I tell you to do
when I'm working?

08:10.369 --> 08:11.370
I'm sorry.

08:11.904 --> 08:14.373
Something urgent came up,
so I had to intrude.

08:15.674 --> 08:16.608
Director An?

08:18.310 --> 08:20.712
I thought you were here because
there was an issue with the construction.

08:20.712 --> 08:21.747
You startled me.

08:22.481 --> 08:24.583
The gallery construction is going well,

08:25.017 --> 08:28.253
and you can expect
a more than satisfactory result.

08:30.122 --> 08:31.824
It seems I interrupted your work.

08:32.491 --> 08:33.392
I'm sorry.

08:34.760 --> 08:36.128
My personality can be a bit...

08:36.495 --> 08:38.197
I make mistakes like this sometimes.

08:38.530 --> 08:39.498
Not at all.

08:50.809 --> 08:53.579
I came because I wanted
to ask your advice.

08:54.446 --> 08:56.181
It's about a friend in the same industry.

08:56.548 --> 08:58.517
He has a bit of a problem.

08:58.884 --> 09:01.053
For you to come
all the way here in person,

09:01.053 --> 09:02.688
you must be quite close.

09:03.188 --> 09:04.022
Yes.

09:04.690 --> 09:07.126
We've known each other since college,
so it's been a long time.

09:08.861 --> 09:11.463
He's very reserved,
so I'm worried about him.

09:12.931 --> 09:14.333
Ask me anything.

09:16.535 --> 09:18.604
This friend has
an important presentation...

09:18.604 --> 09:21.240
coming up for a project.

09:22.207 --> 09:25.010
And during preparations,
he got some help from higher-ups.

09:25.010 --> 09:25.978
Quietly.

09:26.445 --> 09:29.148
But the other side found out.

09:30.983 --> 09:33.085
Well, he hasn't told me much,
so I'm not sure,

09:35.120 --> 09:37.289
but it seems like
he's taken some damage too.

09:40.459 --> 09:42.761
He's a close friend,
and he seems to be struggling a lot.

09:42.761 --> 09:43.729
It's hard...

09:44.296 --> 09:45.264
to watch.

09:46.932 --> 09:49.234
I was wondering how I could help,

09:50.869 --> 09:54.706
and I thought I should ask
a respected senior...

09:54.706 --> 09:55.774
in the industry.

09:57.109 --> 09:58.544
It's not a good example,

09:59.778 --> 10:03.248
but the reality is that things like this
often happen in the industry's shadows.

10:04.116 --> 10:06.118
I'm sure you feel awful
because he's your friend,

10:06.819 --> 10:08.987
but it's better not to get involved
in matters like this.

10:09.221 --> 10:10.155
Even if you step in,

10:10.756 --> 10:13.926
it's rare that anything meaningful
comes of it.

10:15.394 --> 10:16.228
Is that so?

10:16.662 --> 10:17.596
Of course.

10:18.797 --> 10:21.133
Your friend made the first risky move.

10:21.133 --> 10:22.734
I don't see any need for you to step in...

10:23.769 --> 10:25.571
and clean it up, Director An.

10:26.438 --> 10:28.040
Frankly, it isn't possible.

10:29.007 --> 10:30.108
The other side...

10:30.709 --> 10:33.445
won't just stupidly sit there
and take it either.

10:34.146 --> 10:36.715
But there's something
my friend doesn't know.

10:41.687 --> 10:44.990
The other side is using
some serious shortcuts too.

10:46.859 --> 10:48.293
He's cozying up
to a four-term assemblyman,

10:48.293 --> 10:50.129
playing golf with him on sunny days,

10:50.796 --> 10:53.799
and even taking on construction
for his daughter's office building.

10:54.199 --> 10:56.001
He's putting in a lot of effort.

10:58.103 --> 11:01.306
With money and favors, quite passionately.

11:02.641 --> 11:04.376
I think I know...

11:05.377 --> 11:07.312
who this friend of yours is.

11:12.284 --> 11:13.152
Mr. Cho.

11:15.220 --> 11:18.157
At this point, would it be better
for everyone to quietly do their own job,

11:19.892 --> 11:22.494
or would it be better to go all out
and have a nasty fight?

11:23.095 --> 11:24.897
I honestly have no idea.

11:27.466 --> 11:28.567
Which would you recommend?

11:35.974 --> 11:37.476
I have an appointment.

11:37.476 --> 11:38.811
I'll be leaving now.

11:41.847 --> 11:42.714
Right.

11:43.715 --> 11:45.451
Please halt the gallery construction.

11:45.951 --> 11:48.921
I'll wire the costs incurred so far
this afternoon.

11:55.828 --> 11:59.264
(Jigu Electronics)

12:07.039 --> 12:08.173
I got all the money,

12:09.675 --> 12:11.009
and I did as much work as she paid for.

12:11.910 --> 12:12.911
Everyone has...

12:12.911 --> 12:15.280
their own life, right?

12:15.280 --> 12:17.516
So stop having pointless thoughts.

12:24.957 --> 12:25.924
Come on.

12:31.296 --> 12:32.164
Right?

12:32.464 --> 12:33.966
Who am I...

12:33.966 --> 12:35.868
to stick my nose into someone else's life?

12:35.868 --> 12:37.436
Well, I'm sure
they'll figure it out themselves.

12:38.537 --> 12:39.404
Don't do it.

12:40.839 --> 12:42.341
It's hot.

12:55.821 --> 12:56.855
Lee Sang Ho.

12:57.456 --> 12:58.557
If I've drawn my gun,

12:58.557 --> 13:00.692
I have to shoot something,
even if it's a rotten pumpkin.

13:00.692 --> 13:02.961
Extortion, threats, fraud,
taking money by force,

13:02.961 --> 13:04.463
and even assaulting a former cop.

13:04.463 --> 13:06.165
Does it make sense
to just leave a guy who did that alone?

13:10.002 --> 13:11.103
(Gi Cheol)

13:11.103 --> 13:12.638
(There's no such thing
as a good rich bastard.)

13:12.638 --> 13:14.239
(Do you think threatening
a corporate chairman is easy?)

13:14.239 --> 13:15.174
(Ham Myo Jin?)

13:15.374 --> 13:16.642
Sir, you trust me, right?

13:17.543 --> 13:19.812
Please don't do this. Think it over.

13:20.379 --> 13:22.381
Now, we just need to get rid...

13:22.381 --> 13:24.983
of that leech, Ham Myo Jin,
who's clinging to Ryu Jun Ho,

13:25.350 --> 13:27.653
before that bitch sucks everything dry.

13:28.854 --> 13:30.088
I'm warning you.

13:31.824 --> 13:33.358
Leave that girl alone.

13:41.800 --> 13:43.469
Ham Myo Jin...

13:44.169 --> 13:45.471
has another agenda too?

14:23.175 --> 14:25.577
(No recording file found)

14:29.548 --> 14:30.549
You scared me.

14:32.451 --> 14:34.052
That startled me.

14:35.154 --> 14:36.855
Are you awake now?

14:39.391 --> 14:41.026
What happened to me?

14:43.295 --> 14:44.863
You don't remember?

14:45.664 --> 14:47.266
You suddenly
disappeared yesterday, Ms. Ham.

14:47.266 --> 14:48.767
It was chaos.

14:49.134 --> 14:50.702
Where were you wandering around
on your own,

14:50.702 --> 14:51.870
without even telling me?

14:52.571 --> 14:54.139
Well...

14:54.139 --> 14:56.775
Luckily, your phone had location tracking,

14:56.775 --> 14:58.610
so Jun Ho barely managed to find you.

14:58.944 --> 15:00.946
Thank goodness that was there.

15:19.131 --> 15:19.998
I'm sorry.

15:20.232 --> 15:22.468
Why did you go
to such a dangerous neighborhood?

15:23.035 --> 15:24.736
It's a redevelopment area,
so it's deserted,

15:24.736 --> 15:26.472
and everyone has already moved away.

15:26.705 --> 15:28.073
I don't remember anything.

15:29.041 --> 15:31.076
Do you really not know...

15:31.076 --> 15:32.611
what you did there?

15:35.781 --> 15:37.249
No.

15:38.884 --> 15:39.985
Then,

15:40.385 --> 15:41.887
I wonder if anyone saw you.

15:42.721 --> 15:45.457
I heard there are still
a few people who haven't moved out.

15:45.991 --> 15:47.025
Jun Ho said so.

15:53.966 --> 15:56.001
Wherever you go, you should contact me,

15:56.001 --> 15:57.503
or at least leave a text.

15:57.503 --> 15:59.138
Jun Ho told me to pack my things
and leave immediately,

15:59.138 --> 16:01.406
but I begged him and barely got past it.

16:01.840 --> 16:03.008
I'm really sorry.

16:03.642 --> 16:06.512
I'm partly at fault too. I left you alone.

16:07.446 --> 16:09.381
Where is Jun Ho now?

16:09.915 --> 16:11.083
Call him.

16:11.416 --> 16:12.785
If he hears you're awake,

16:12.785 --> 16:15.287
he'll come flying over
no matter where he is.

16:16.789 --> 16:17.623
Yes.

16:17.890 --> 16:19.324
Anyway, get some rest.

16:19.625 --> 16:20.959
You need to eat something.

16:21.994 --> 16:23.061
I'll bring something.

16:38.777 --> 16:39.978
Pick up.

16:39.978 --> 16:41.713
Pick up.

16:45.217 --> 16:47.453
- The customer is currently unavailable...
- Damn it.

16:47.719 --> 16:48.687
(Idiot Woo Sik)

16:49.822 --> 16:50.689
Damn it.

16:51.990 --> 16:53.125
Seriously?

16:53.525 --> 16:55.527
Is this bastard
missing a few screws or what?

17:01.200 --> 17:02.835
- The customer is currently unavailable...
- Damn it.

17:27.726 --> 17:29.895
Are you awake, you kidnapper?

17:30.429 --> 17:31.697
You were next anyway.

17:32.564 --> 17:34.600
Wait.

17:36.068 --> 17:38.937
If I did anything wrong to you two...

17:38.937 --> 17:41.573
Hey, if you don't know, how would I?

17:42.141 --> 17:43.375
We don't have time.

17:44.343 --> 17:45.177
Boss.

17:45.577 --> 17:46.678
This bastard...

17:46.678 --> 17:48.847
was getting beaten too much
to understand the situation.

17:49.848 --> 17:50.682
Yes?

17:50.682 --> 17:53.018
Do you know how many Chinese customers...

17:53.018 --> 17:54.386
came to the store today and left?

17:54.820 --> 17:56.655
Those rich Chinese people.

17:57.122 --> 18:00.125
You kicked away a pile of money
that walked in on its own,

18:00.125 --> 18:02.060
and you still call yourself a businessman?

18:02.060 --> 18:03.629
You damn idiot.

18:07.866 --> 18:09.568
I'm truly sorry. I deserve to die.

18:09.568 --> 18:11.136
Please, just spare my life.

18:12.771 --> 18:15.140
Bastards who sell people...

18:15.140 --> 18:17.075
all say the same thing.

18:17.643 --> 18:19.711
So forget it the moment you hear it.

18:19.711 --> 18:20.512
What?

18:20.512 --> 18:23.649
Was it nice
scamming those innocent people?

18:24.750 --> 18:26.685
A useless piece of trash like you...

18:26.685 --> 18:28.287
beat up my brother and stole his money?

18:28.787 --> 18:30.756
Hand over every penny you have...

18:30.756 --> 18:31.824
and leave quietly.

18:33.425 --> 18:34.893
Where did you spend
all the money you made?

18:35.294 --> 18:36.862
You secretly ate it all
behind your partner's back.

18:36.862 --> 18:37.930
Did it fill your belly?

18:38.630 --> 18:40.699
I have something to tell you.

18:41.733 --> 18:42.901
I only did what I was told.

18:42.901 --> 18:44.470
Someone else took all the money.

18:44.470 --> 18:47.239
My bankbook and seal were taken too.
I have nothing.

18:47.239 --> 18:48.907
Bullshit.

18:48.907 --> 18:49.908
Just kill him.

18:50.509 --> 18:52.611
It's true.

18:52.611 --> 18:54.746
I barely make a living running a tiny bar,

18:54.746 --> 18:56.215
but somehow I got mixed up in this,

18:56.215 --> 18:58.617
so that vicious boss takes
every penny I earn.

18:58.617 --> 19:00.319
Your boss must be happy, being rich.

19:00.319 --> 19:01.220
Right?

19:01.487 --> 19:04.523
Even now, my boss is stuck
to some mentally ill woman...

19:04.523 --> 19:06.792
because that woman's husband
is a construction tycoon.

19:07.292 --> 19:08.293
My boss and that husband
are working together...

19:08.293 --> 19:09.895
to get rid of that woman right now.

19:12.297 --> 19:13.832
A rich bastard is trying to kill his wife?

19:13.832 --> 19:15.501
- Yes.
- And your boss is helping him?

19:15.501 --> 19:17.269
My boss is no ordinary villain.

19:17.269 --> 19:19.972
My boss will probably score big from this
and run off overseas.

19:19.972 --> 19:22.407
Then I won't get my money either.

19:23.275 --> 19:24.276
Where is your boss?

19:25.144 --> 19:27.980
You're saying that weasel-like bastard
has Hae Sik's money?

19:28.280 --> 19:29.848
Yes, that's right.

19:38.056 --> 19:39.458
If we meet your boss,

19:40.459 --> 19:42.261
we can get the money right away?

19:42.528 --> 19:43.595
Of course.

19:43.595 --> 19:45.230
If you come with me,
I'll get those two bastards...

19:45.230 --> 19:47.366
to pay your brother's money,
interest, damages,

19:47.366 --> 19:48.567
all of it.

19:50.602 --> 19:53.038
I'll prove what I'm saying
by calling right now.

19:53.038 --> 19:55.207
If even a little bit of it isn't true,

19:55.207 --> 19:57.643
you can do whatever you want
with my money and my body.

19:57.943 --> 19:59.545
I'll even write it in blood.

20:10.055 --> 20:11.023
Do it.

20:12.224 --> 20:13.692
We don't have time.

20:13.692 --> 20:15.727
Whether they answer or not,

20:16.161 --> 20:17.196
you get one call.

20:24.303 --> 20:26.171
You go find a plastic bag.

20:26.171 --> 20:27.206
Yes.

20:27.206 --> 20:28.974
We're going to ruin all our clothes
because of the blood.

20:34.513 --> 20:35.447
Where is it?

20:35.447 --> 20:36.582
Ri A.

20:47.493 --> 20:48.894
What do you think you're doing right now?

20:49.495 --> 20:52.631
Were you hiding somewhere
reflecting for days?

20:52.631 --> 20:53.532
At least you know you should be ashamed.

20:53.532 --> 20:54.466
Hey, enough.

20:54.967 --> 20:56.702
I can't work with you anymore,

20:57.336 --> 20:58.804
so bring back all the money
you took from me.

20:59.538 --> 21:01.106
You must've been pretty shocked.

21:01.573 --> 21:03.308
That's what you get
for not doing as told...

21:03.308 --> 21:05.043
and doing whatever you want.

21:05.043 --> 21:06.979
Shut up and bring me my money.

21:06.979 --> 21:07.813
Money?

21:08.280 --> 21:09.648
You're talking about money?

21:09.648 --> 21:10.649
Because you didn't listen to me,

21:10.649 --> 21:12.251
you haven't even done
one thing right so far.

21:12.251 --> 21:14.553
While I'm asking nicely,
give me back my bankbook and seal.

21:15.521 --> 21:18.023
Bring back all the money
you stole from me, you thieving bitch!

21:21.026 --> 21:23.662
Stop talking bullshit, Woo Sik.

21:23.662 --> 21:25.297
Let me explain it to you again.

21:25.831 --> 21:27.332
You ran away because of gambling debts,

21:27.332 --> 21:29.201
and you only survived because of me.

21:29.468 --> 21:30.402
Hey.

21:30.402 --> 21:32.504
I clearly told you to run.

21:32.504 --> 21:34.239
You ruined everything yourself,
and now you're asking for money?

21:34.606 --> 21:35.474
Your bankbook?

21:35.474 --> 21:36.508
You want your seal back?

21:37.743 --> 21:40.312
What a brilliant move it was
to keep them in my hands.

21:47.820 --> 21:49.221
Your boss is a woman?

21:52.825 --> 21:53.692
Yes.

21:54.626 --> 21:57.396
The history of metal is,
in effect, the history of humankind.

21:57.796 --> 21:59.498
That is an undeniable fact.

21:59.932 --> 22:02.134
Humanity's brilliant achievements...

22:02.134 --> 22:04.470
were possible because metal existed.

22:07.372 --> 22:09.107
Even in this small phone,

22:09.508 --> 22:12.845
there is aluminum, cobalt,
tin, and palladium.

22:12.845 --> 22:14.780
An astonishing number of metals...

22:15.113 --> 22:16.748
are part of our everyday lives.

22:18.717 --> 22:20.319
For this museum,

22:20.319 --> 22:22.788
I want to invite in metal, the outsider.

22:22.788 --> 22:24.823
Metal was once treated as nothing more...

22:24.823 --> 22:26.725
than a structural support for buildings.

22:27.359 --> 22:30.262
The countless people from Korea and abroad
who visit this museum...

22:30.729 --> 22:32.831
have their own cultures and languages.

22:32.831 --> 22:34.032
They are outsiders.

22:34.600 --> 22:37.603
Just as music is a language
that unites the world,

22:38.437 --> 22:40.939
metal has long been
a common language of humankind.

22:41.306 --> 22:43.008
We thought they were different,

22:43.509 --> 22:44.676
but they are not.

22:46.712 --> 22:48.046
The meeting of metal and music...

22:48.947 --> 22:50.649
will create new solidarity and fusion...

22:51.316 --> 22:53.685
with the outsiders who visit this museum.

22:53.685 --> 22:55.654
That is what I firmly believe.

22:56.388 --> 22:57.289
My theme...

22:58.023 --> 22:59.958
is "Strange Yet Familiar."

23:11.003 --> 23:13.305
A museum is not a new space.

23:13.305 --> 23:16.275
People think they know museums well,

23:16.275 --> 23:17.943
even if they are not familiar.

23:17.943 --> 23:19.845
So even without going there,

23:19.845 --> 23:21.446
they believe they know
what will be there...

23:21.446 --> 23:22.648
and what kind of experience awaits.

23:22.648 --> 23:24.750
They see it as a place they can predict.

23:25.584 --> 23:28.587
That place, neither new nor moving,

23:29.021 --> 23:31.123
why do people still visit it?

23:31.590 --> 23:33.091
A space like that called a museum.

23:33.091 --> 23:36.061
Why must we build one again now?

23:36.495 --> 23:39.298
I felt I needed to consider the reason.

23:41.333 --> 23:42.167
Memory!

23:46.138 --> 23:48.607
The memory people will encounter here!

23:49.942 --> 23:51.910
People come here...

23:51.910 --> 23:54.513
to encounter that memory
they want to keep for a lifetime.

23:55.113 --> 23:56.682
In this museum,

23:56.682 --> 24:00.119
the more brightly the memory of every
piece of content they encounter shines,

24:00.119 --> 24:02.354
the more people will return.

24:02.354 --> 24:05.624
That is why a museum must give people...

24:05.624 --> 24:08.494
a good memory they will never forget.

24:09.862 --> 24:11.029
The theme of my work...

24:12.064 --> 24:13.298
is "A Place for Memory."

24:16.235 --> 24:17.603
May I ask you a question?

24:18.504 --> 24:21.273
Is there a memory as powerful
as the one you just described...

24:22.040 --> 24:23.742
that you also carry?

24:24.643 --> 24:27.279
One you'd want to include in this museum.

24:42.027 --> 24:43.328
I'm fine,

24:44.096 --> 24:45.063
so please tell me.

24:46.198 --> 24:48.333
It's not good.

24:49.234 --> 24:51.403
It's terminal pancreatic cancer.

24:59.511 --> 25:01.613
It has already spread
throughout your body,

25:02.181 --> 25:04.416
so surgery would be meaningless.

25:06.151 --> 25:07.386
Is there a reason...

25:07.386 --> 25:09.488
you didn't come to the hospital
until your body got this bad?

25:12.090 --> 25:14.259
I was just busy.

25:16.595 --> 25:18.230
How much time do I have?

25:19.465 --> 25:20.866
Three months at most.

25:22.768 --> 25:25.304
Realistically, it'll be less than that.

25:26.605 --> 25:28.707
I'm sorry to say this,

25:29.274 --> 25:31.410
but to the people you can tell,

25:31.410 --> 25:33.045
it's best to tell them in advance.

25:33.445 --> 25:36.148
With your body in this condition,
we don't know what might happen or when.

25:36.148 --> 25:38.317
So doing that will help you.

25:39.585 --> 25:41.487
Please don't drink alcohol.

25:41.753 --> 25:43.822
You should at least ease the pain
in the time you have left.

25:51.130 --> 25:52.931
You'll need more painkillers.

25:53.532 --> 25:54.800
I'll prescribe them for you.

25:55.200 --> 25:56.268
Since you're giving them anyway,

25:57.202 --> 25:58.570
give me the strong ones.

25:59.338 --> 26:00.339
Plenty of them.

26:01.740 --> 26:04.209
Since I won't be coming to see you again.

26:07.813 --> 26:08.647
(Personal Information - Ryu Jun Ho)

26:08.647 --> 26:10.082
(2022 Founded Mono Architecture)

26:10.082 --> 26:12.751
A scholarship student
in Brown's architecture department,

26:12.751 --> 26:14.620
with a minor in economics.

26:15.721 --> 26:18.924
He came to Korea
and founded Mono Architecture.

26:19.725 --> 26:21.493
Young Architect Award.

26:22.194 --> 26:24.062
He won it two years in a row.

26:24.563 --> 26:26.598
His life is a straight path to success.

26:26.598 --> 26:27.900
He must have nothing to envy.

26:29.701 --> 26:30.569
Sir.

26:30.803 --> 26:33.071
Don't you think this feels
a little too dramatic?

26:33.739 --> 26:35.741
That Ryu Jun Ho left the country...

26:35.741 --> 26:37.810
right before the villa accident?

26:37.810 --> 26:40.712
He was in Germany
on the day of the accident.

26:41.213 --> 26:42.781
There are even immigration records.

26:42.781 --> 26:44.183
What better alibi could there be?

26:46.285 --> 26:48.887
But the chief says we should ignore that.

26:48.887 --> 26:50.956
The chief does have a point.

26:51.490 --> 26:54.660
If those two set their minds to it,
what couldn't they scheme up?

26:54.660 --> 26:56.995
And the woman has ironclad memory loss.

26:57.796 --> 26:59.131
They're untouchable.

27:00.098 --> 27:01.066
Forget that.

27:02.201 --> 27:03.769
Ryu Jun Ho and Ham Myo Jin.

27:03.769 --> 27:05.003
In the middle of all this,

27:05.003 --> 27:07.139
I'm more curious
why those two are living together.

27:08.240 --> 27:09.408
Business partners?

27:10.476 --> 27:12.544
A love story against the world?

27:14.880 --> 27:17.749
They must know staying together
will only make the police more suspicious.

27:17.749 --> 27:19.218
They know that perfectly well.

27:20.052 --> 27:22.154
I don't understand why they're doing this.

27:22.521 --> 27:25.591
Then why are we going
to meet Ryu Jun Ho now?

27:26.191 --> 27:27.359
We have to find out...

27:28.160 --> 27:29.294
whether it's business...

27:30.195 --> 27:31.296
or a love story.

27:32.231 --> 27:33.699
You have arrived at your destination.

27:33.699 --> 27:34.633
Is this it?

27:45.377 --> 27:46.311
That bastard.

27:46.879 --> 27:49.681
I guess he really is loaded.

28:00.492 --> 28:03.428
I know you must be busy.
Thank you for making time.

28:03.829 --> 28:05.731
If I can help, I should.

28:05.964 --> 28:07.232
For the investigation,

28:07.232 --> 28:10.636
I may have to ask you
some uncomfortable questions.

28:10.636 --> 28:12.271
Please understand.

28:12.905 --> 28:14.039
I'll try.

28:15.007 --> 28:17.843
Sir, what do you think
about Ms. Ham's accident,

28:17.843 --> 28:19.978
in terms of the place and time?

28:21.713 --> 28:24.082
Do you think it's something
that could reasonably happen?

28:24.283 --> 28:26.218
I'm curious too...

28:26.218 --> 28:28.654
why Myo Jin was there at that hour.

28:30.989 --> 28:34.059
But we haven't talked about that yet.

28:34.460 --> 28:36.161
She lost her memory in that accident,

28:36.161 --> 28:38.297
and she's receiving treatment.

28:38.297 --> 28:39.231
So I'm worried...

28:40.032 --> 28:41.166
it might give her...

28:41.934 --> 28:43.602
an even greater shock.

28:46.472 --> 28:49.074
Does that mean you'll wait
for her treatment to progress...

28:49.074 --> 28:50.642
before asking her?

28:53.745 --> 28:55.047
The best way...

28:56.248 --> 28:58.283
would be for it to come out
in the police investigation.

29:01.453 --> 29:03.555
That would be the right way, yes.

29:06.291 --> 29:08.026
I'll also need to ask...

29:08.594 --> 29:10.529
a few questions about the villa accident.

29:12.231 --> 29:15.834
You were engaged
to the late Ms. Choi Hee Su quite early.

29:17.569 --> 29:18.537
Hee Su wanted it.

29:18.537 --> 29:20.506
When we first visited your home,

29:21.006 --> 29:23.976
why didn't you mention your relationship
with the late Ms. Choi?

29:24.676 --> 29:27.212
It's something that could
easily cause misunderstandings.

29:30.716 --> 29:33.185
Are you asking
about my private life right now?

29:35.754 --> 29:36.622
That day,

29:37.222 --> 29:40.592
weren't you there
to investigate Myo Jin's accident?

29:40.592 --> 29:41.760
That's true,

29:42.561 --> 29:45.097
but this is a question
I have to ask again now.

29:46.632 --> 29:47.566
Is that so?

29:51.036 --> 29:52.104
Who knows?

29:53.272 --> 29:54.973
If you, detective,

29:56.074 --> 29:57.843
had conducted...

29:57.843 --> 30:00.445
a calmer and more considerate
interview that day,

30:00.445 --> 30:01.313
perhaps...

30:02.080 --> 30:03.649
Hee Su's story might have come up too.

30:03.649 --> 30:05.951
The truth is,
it does bother us quite a bit.

30:06.852 --> 30:08.520
The late Ms. Choi...

30:09.087 --> 30:11.190
and you were in a common-law relationship,

30:11.190 --> 30:13.058
and now, you're living...

30:13.058 --> 30:15.761
with Ms. Ham, who was Ms. Choi's friend.

30:16.195 --> 30:18.430
You may see it that way, detective,

30:19.965 --> 30:20.899
but...

30:21.633 --> 30:24.036
we respected one another's choices...

30:24.036 --> 30:25.771
and sincerely supported each other.

30:26.939 --> 30:27.906
I hope...

30:29.274 --> 30:32.044
you won't look at the three of us
through such a strange lens.

30:36.014 --> 30:39.284
The day of the villa explosion
was a special day, wasn't it?

30:39.284 --> 30:40.285
It was Hee Su's birthday.

30:40.285 --> 30:42.020
And yet you went to Germany.

30:42.321 --> 30:45.891
Coincidentally, the day before
the birthday when the accident happened.

30:45.891 --> 30:48.060
I had no choice
because of a conference schedule.

30:48.894 --> 30:50.395
Even so, how could you...

30:50.395 --> 30:51.363
Detective.

30:51.597 --> 30:52.764
At this point,

30:52.764 --> 30:55.033
I believe I've answered...

30:55.033 --> 30:56.535
enough of the uncomfortable questions
you mentioned.

30:57.035 --> 30:57.903
Didn't you come today...

30:58.470 --> 31:01.006
about Myo Jin's accident investigation?

31:06.712 --> 31:07.713
I'm sorry.

31:07.980 --> 31:10.115
I have an urgent schedule,
so I should get going.

31:13.886 --> 31:15.320
If there's more to discuss,

31:15.320 --> 31:17.156
let's set another date.

31:17.156 --> 31:19.958
Thank you for taking your valuable time.

31:20.526 --> 31:22.961
Please understand
if we bother you a few more times.

31:23.428 --> 31:25.164
It seems you still have
a lot of questions.

31:25.764 --> 31:26.832
Actually,

31:28.233 --> 31:30.836
unlike Chairman Choi Young Ho,
who died in the fire,

31:30.836 --> 31:31.870
Ms. Choi...

31:32.404 --> 31:34.473
was murdered
with a stab wound to the neck.

31:35.874 --> 31:37.176
The villa accident...

31:37.176 --> 31:39.912
was a murder case disguised as a fire.

31:40.546 --> 31:41.914
Murder?

31:43.182 --> 31:44.049
Yes.

31:44.049 --> 31:45.017
That's right.

31:47.753 --> 31:48.787
Are you certain?

31:50.589 --> 31:53.225
Judging by the pattern
of the wound and its depth,

31:54.026 --> 31:56.228
there's a strong possibility
it was a revenge killing.

32:01.066 --> 32:02.234
The National Forensic Service...

32:02.234 --> 32:05.437
is fully reexamining
the materials from the accident scene,

32:05.437 --> 32:06.271
so...

32:06.805 --> 32:09.107
we'll likely identify the suspect soon.

32:21.954 --> 32:24.256
How can someone change that much?

32:24.256 --> 32:26.358
He's completely different
from when we first saw him.

32:26.925 --> 32:28.227
He sees right through us...

32:28.560 --> 32:31.396
like he already knew when we would come...

32:31.396 --> 32:33.132
and what we would ask.

32:33.132 --> 32:35.968
Still, when he heard
Choi Hee Su had been murdered,

32:35.968 --> 32:36.935
he lost it.

32:38.604 --> 32:40.205
I don't think he expected that...

32:40.672 --> 32:42.241
because even his face changed color.

32:43.242 --> 32:45.177
Seeing him today,

32:45.544 --> 32:47.846
I realized he was acting in front of us
when we first saw him.

32:47.846 --> 32:48.680
Isn't that right?

32:49.882 --> 32:51.483
Ham Myo Jin and Ryu Jun Ho.

32:53.452 --> 32:54.953
Maybe both of them were.

33:03.996 --> 33:05.497
Ri A sent this,

33:05.497 --> 33:06.665
saying you absolutely had to see it.

33:10.035 --> 33:11.036
Headquarters...

33:11.737 --> 33:14.173
has contracted with the audit team
of the top company in Korea.

33:15.374 --> 33:16.809
Since it's the vice chairman's order,

33:17.209 --> 33:18.677
we're definitely the target.

33:20.546 --> 33:21.847
This competition.

33:24.183 --> 33:25.117
Do I...

33:26.485 --> 33:27.686
really need it?

33:31.023 --> 33:31.990
It's ridiculous, isn't it?

33:33.525 --> 33:35.360
That I'm thinking like this now.

33:42.701 --> 33:44.670
I believe it's an opportunity
worth staking everything you have on,

33:45.971 --> 33:48.173
and a once-in-a-lifetime chance, sir.

33:49.508 --> 33:51.210
Once this museum is completed,

33:51.610 --> 33:53.412
you'll rise to the top of the industry.

34:03.155 --> 34:05.023
As an architect,

34:06.892 --> 34:08.127
yes, I suppose.

34:11.263 --> 34:12.197
Definitely.

34:50.669 --> 34:52.337
(Wang Gi Cheol)

34:52.337 --> 34:53.505
(Don't let your guard down.)

34:53.505 --> 34:55.007
(They're far smarter than you or me.)

34:58.710 --> 35:00.012
(Approached Choi Hee Su's fiancé
Name, Ryu Jun Ho)

35:00.012 --> 35:01.413
(Chairman Choi Young Ho
funded Ryu Jun Ho's business.)

35:01.413 --> 35:02.848
(Company name, Mono Architecture)

35:02.848 --> 35:04.416
(Using Choi Hee Su and Ryu Jun Ho
to track Chairman Choi's whereabouts)

35:04.416 --> 35:05.684
(Neither of them has noticed.)

35:18.063 --> 35:19.865
(Atibam)

35:23.535 --> 35:24.670
(Atibam)

35:24.670 --> 35:27.573
(Atibam Tablet Lorazepam)

35:27.573 --> 35:28.674
(Neuropsychiatric drug)

35:28.674 --> 35:31.677
(Indicated for treating
patients with schizophrenia)

35:35.814 --> 35:37.015
(Clazapam)

35:40.586 --> 35:42.321
(Clazapam Clozapine,
neuropsychiatric drug)

35:42.321 --> 35:46.825
(Panic disorder prevention,
reduced onset of depression)

35:50.262 --> 35:53.632
From now on, I plan to keep
only basic medication treatment...

35:54.299 --> 35:55.868
because despite the test results,

35:57.002 --> 36:00.906
your condition is already
no different from a normal person's.

36:23.295 --> 36:24.396
I'm sure of it.

36:24.897 --> 36:27.399
There's something so huge
behind the Choi Hee Su case...

36:27.399 --> 36:28.901
that everything else can't compare.

36:29.668 --> 36:31.069
That bastard Lee Jong Su...

36:31.069 --> 36:32.538
knows how to stir up Wang Gi Cheol...

36:33.105 --> 36:35.941
and the leverage to extort money
from Chairman Choi.

36:36.275 --> 36:38.744
I need to catch that bastard
who beat the hell out of me,

36:39.244 --> 36:41.146
break him down
and dig out the whole story.

36:43.682 --> 36:45.984
This is the last time.

36:45.984 --> 36:47.553
Just once, and I'll never do it again.

36:47.953 --> 36:48.821
I mean it.

36:49.421 --> 36:52.391
Just once.

36:52.724 --> 36:55.427
(Central Municipal Hospital)

37:04.736 --> 37:05.904
What brings you here?

37:06.371 --> 37:07.739
It isn't visiting hours right now.

37:09.107 --> 37:10.142
Police.

37:10.476 --> 37:13.045
I'm here because there's
something urgent I need to confirm.

37:15.147 --> 37:17.249
Do I need to show you this?

37:20.552 --> 37:22.855
May I see...

37:23.522 --> 37:24.623
patient Lee Jong Su?

37:39.571 --> 37:41.440
Even if you're police, by regulation,

37:41.440 --> 37:43.342
visits without prior notice
aren't allowed.

37:43.642 --> 37:45.444
I'm sorry, but please come back tomorrow.

37:45.444 --> 37:46.979
I see.

37:47.312 --> 37:48.413
There's nothing I can do, then.

37:48.413 --> 37:51.617
Then could you at least
connect me to the officer...

37:51.617 --> 37:53.519
on duty outside his room?

37:55.921 --> 37:57.656
I'll just relay instructions and leave.

37:59.625 --> 38:00.459
Yes.

38:04.963 --> 38:05.898
This is the duty room.

38:06.632 --> 38:09.101
Please connect me to the officer assigned...

38:09.101 --> 38:10.035
to patient Lee Jong Su in Room 8111.

38:10.302 --> 38:11.136
Yes.

38:12.738 --> 38:14.807
Please wait a moment.
You'll be connected shortly.

38:15.107 --> 38:15.974
Thank you.

38:16.341 --> 38:18.677
May I use the restroom?

38:29.054 --> 38:30.522
Great job you guys are doing.

38:31.123 --> 38:32.691
You bastards are slacking off.

38:44.770 --> 38:46.672
You've got it easy, don't you?

38:47.372 --> 38:48.407
Here you are...

38:51.410 --> 38:52.177
What?

39:00.686 --> 39:01.720
Lee Jong Su.

39:04.823 --> 39:06.024
Lee Jong Su.

39:06.024 --> 39:07.226
Stop right there.

39:07.226 --> 39:08.894
Damn it, that bastard.

39:10.896 --> 39:11.730
Stop right there!

39:20.038 --> 39:21.273
Is that bastard really a patient?

39:22.307 --> 39:23.142
Stop right there.

39:30.816 --> 39:31.884
Come on.

39:32.718 --> 39:33.919
Got you, you bastard.

39:36.155 --> 39:36.989
You bit me.

39:36.989 --> 39:39.124
You son of a bitch.

39:39.424 --> 39:40.325
Come on.

39:43.228 --> 39:44.329
Should I wait? What do I do?

39:44.329 --> 39:45.364
Should I wait? What do I do?

39:46.064 --> 39:46.965
Damn it.

39:48.400 --> 39:49.501
You there, sir.

39:50.502 --> 39:51.703
Where are you coming from?

39:54.072 --> 39:55.174
Is something going on?

39:57.976 --> 39:58.777
Sir.

39:59.778 --> 40:00.612
Catch him!

40:02.414 --> 40:03.315
Catch him!

40:07.686 --> 40:09.087
Why are you doing this?

40:09.087 --> 40:10.088
Why are you running away?

40:10.088 --> 40:11.924
That man over there is trying to...

40:13.459 --> 40:14.426
You punk.

40:14.760 --> 40:15.928
You're dead today.

40:16.628 --> 40:17.629
There he is. That's him.

40:18.997 --> 40:19.865
You bastard.

40:20.365 --> 40:21.266
Stop right there.

40:27.673 --> 40:28.507
You.

40:30.509 --> 40:32.010
Lee Jong Su.

40:32.010 --> 40:32.811
Stop right there.

40:36.682 --> 40:38.016
What's the reason?

40:38.016 --> 40:39.318
Why are you using Wang Gi Cheol...

40:39.318 --> 40:41.153
to threaten Chairman Choi, Ham Myo Jin,

40:41.153 --> 40:43.355
and Ryu Jun Ho?

40:43.355 --> 40:45.591
If you don't want to eat
prison food for life,

40:45.591 --> 40:46.692
talk right now.

40:46.692 --> 40:47.893
Bullshit.

40:47.893 --> 40:49.027
You're not a cop, are you?

40:49.027 --> 40:50.462
You son of a bitch.

40:52.264 --> 40:53.565
What?

40:53.565 --> 40:54.600
Why are you grabbing me?

40:54.600 --> 40:56.034
I'm not the one you should catch. He is.

40:56.034 --> 40:58.270
I'm telling you, arrest him, not me.

40:58.871 --> 41:00.372
He's the one
who impersonated a police officer.

41:00.372 --> 41:01.440
Arrest him immediately.

41:01.940 --> 41:03.208
He said he would kill me.

41:03.208 --> 41:04.409
Please save me.

41:04.409 --> 41:06.044
Don't worry. You're safe now.

41:06.044 --> 41:07.779
Hey, you idiots.

41:07.779 --> 41:09.348
Can't you see he's putting on a show?

41:09.348 --> 41:11.316
I said he's the one you should arrest.

41:11.316 --> 41:12.484
You must be insane.

41:12.484 --> 41:14.586
Go say that at the police station.

41:14.820 --> 41:16.955
I'll explain everything.

41:16.955 --> 41:19.024
Arrest that guy first, all right?

41:19.024 --> 41:21.193
Arrest me and that guy together.

41:21.193 --> 41:23.262
- Who do you think you're ordering around?
- Let's go to the station together.

41:23.262 --> 41:24.329
- Put him in the car.
- Yes, sir.

41:24.329 --> 41:26.331
It's not me you should arrest.

41:26.799 --> 41:28.433
- Hey, let go!
- Go.

41:39.578 --> 41:42.347
I feel good every time...

41:44.149 --> 41:45.083
because...

41:45.884 --> 41:47.786
you're different from the others.

41:51.790 --> 41:54.259
You seem to have a lot on your mind.

41:54.860 --> 41:57.830
It couldn't have been easy
to come here like this.

42:08.540 --> 42:09.608
After today,

42:09.608 --> 42:11.210
I won't be reachable for a while.

42:11.977 --> 42:14.413
It's because of
the solution I have in mind,

42:14.746 --> 42:15.814
so please understand.

42:33.532 --> 42:34.867
Will you be all right?

42:36.368 --> 42:38.103
They're not easy people,

42:38.370 --> 42:40.139
so things could get ugly.

42:40.873 --> 42:42.007
I have a request.

42:43.175 --> 42:44.009
Yes?

42:45.777 --> 42:46.912
Don't stop...

42:49.248 --> 42:50.549
until I ask you to.

42:53.552 --> 42:54.486
What if...

42:55.287 --> 42:56.421
someone dies?

43:01.026 --> 43:02.327
Then there's nothing we can do.

43:34.259 --> 43:36.028
I told Jun Ho...

43:36.028 --> 43:38.030
that you woke up
and that you're resting now.

43:39.631 --> 43:41.533
Sharp-tongued Ryu Jun Ho said...

43:41.533 --> 43:43.836
that if you don't take your meds properly,

43:44.870 --> 43:47.339
no, that if your condition gets
even slightly worse from now on,

43:47.339 --> 43:48.674
I have to pack my bags immediately.

43:50.843 --> 43:52.177
I'm sorry for putting you
in a difficult position.

43:54.713 --> 43:56.348
It's honestly annoying.

43:56.648 --> 43:59.017
You're probably
the only one in Korea, Ms. Ham.

43:59.685 --> 44:00.519
What do you mean?

44:00.919 --> 44:04.089
Who can make cold-blooded Ryu Jun Ho
smile, be gentle,

44:04.089 --> 44:05.524
and actually care about someone.

44:08.060 --> 44:09.094
Here, take this.

44:09.595 --> 44:10.863
I have to report back.

44:16.401 --> 44:17.903
This isn't what I used to take.

44:18.837 --> 44:19.905
I don't really know.

44:20.405 --> 44:22.207
Jun Ho said the hospital changed
your medication.

44:22.875 --> 44:25.177
He said he went alone
because he thought it'd be hard for you.

44:26.545 --> 44:27.513
Hurry up and take it.

44:32.684 --> 44:34.586
I definitely gave it to you.

45:52.464 --> 45:53.999
I'm telling you, that's not it.

45:55.100 --> 45:56.935
My gut has never been wrong.

46:00.139 --> 46:01.540
Yeah, that's true.

46:07.613 --> 46:08.680
I told you clearly...

46:08.680 --> 46:10.649
that Ham Myo Jin is back to normal.

46:11.216 --> 46:13.619
But isn't it terrifying
that she's pretending she isn't?

46:16.488 --> 46:18.891
Look, you frustrating CEO Ryu Jun Ho.

46:19.525 --> 46:21.994
She must have some scheme.
That's why she's doing it.

46:23.896 --> 46:26.365
You saw that text
and you can still say that?

46:27.065 --> 46:28.600
Hand her over to the police right now.

46:28.600 --> 46:31.303
Use personal protection
or whatever excuse. Just get rid of her.

46:34.840 --> 46:35.908
What kind of trouble are you asking for...

46:35.908 --> 46:38.043
sticking with that woman?

46:41.914 --> 46:43.348
I'm telling you, I saw it.

46:51.089 --> 46:52.724
Go straight up that way and you'll see it.

46:53.625 --> 46:56.261
A gray two-story house
with a parking lot on the first floor.

46:57.529 --> 46:58.897
What does that boss look like?

47:02.468 --> 47:03.735
(Ri A)

47:03.735 --> 47:04.636
Here.

47:05.704 --> 47:07.339
She's not my type either.

47:08.373 --> 47:10.275
Why are you talking to a photo like that?

47:11.143 --> 47:12.277
Do you know her?

47:13.178 --> 47:14.079
No, sir.

47:15.214 --> 47:16.448
What do we do now?

47:18.484 --> 47:20.018
Have you already forgotten
what we came to do?

47:22.621 --> 47:23.689
I'll be back.

47:24.756 --> 47:26.992
What about her male partner?

47:31.663 --> 47:33.031
What was his name again?

47:33.999 --> 47:35.067
Ryu Jun Ho.

47:35.567 --> 47:36.468
Ryu Jun Ho?

47:39.571 --> 47:40.873
Bring him too.

47:41.039 --> 47:42.574
Why do we need that guy?

47:43.308 --> 47:45.043
If we only bring the woman boss,

47:45.043 --> 47:46.879
and she says he has all the money,
what then?

47:48.914 --> 47:49.815
Understood.

47:53.385 --> 47:54.319
Are you going alone?

47:57.222 --> 47:58.157
Are you coming too, boss?

47:58.690 --> 47:59.525
Should I?

48:02.361 --> 48:04.263
Use that bastard to lure them out
and bring them quietly.

48:06.231 --> 48:06.999
Me?

48:09.234 --> 48:10.302
What are you doing?

48:10.302 --> 48:11.336
Okay.

48:16.608 --> 48:17.409
Hey.

48:18.010 --> 48:19.211
This isn't our neighborhood.

48:19.211 --> 48:20.179
Don't make noise.

48:20.179 --> 48:22.047
I don't do anything
you tell me not to, boss.

48:27.219 --> 48:29.688
Use nice words
and bring that boss of yours out first.

48:30.255 --> 48:32.458
If you try anything funny,
I might kill all of you.

48:33.125 --> 48:33.926
It's her.

48:34.793 --> 48:36.328
She's my type.

48:36.328 --> 48:38.630
If we had time, we could've had
something mutually beneficial.

48:39.765 --> 48:43.068
Consider yourself lucky
and stop selling people.

48:44.236 --> 48:45.270
But...

48:45.771 --> 48:46.538
What?

48:46.538 --> 48:48.440
You little...

48:52.311 --> 48:53.645
Damn it.

48:55.247 --> 48:56.181
Hey.

48:57.950 --> 48:58.750
Hey.

48:59.418 --> 49:01.353
Did you think...

49:02.020 --> 49:03.555
you'd be safe without killing me?

49:04.123 --> 49:05.657
You annoying bastard.

49:19.004 --> 49:20.539
Why won't you answer your phone?

49:22.274 --> 49:23.742
Are you looking for your lackeys?

49:24.576 --> 49:25.744
Damn it.

49:30.749 --> 49:31.617
You bastard.

49:39.758 --> 49:40.592
Come here.

49:43.195 --> 49:44.029
Get lost.

49:44.463 --> 49:45.430
You bastard.

49:47.199 --> 49:48.033
Let go.

49:48.600 --> 49:49.368
Let go!

49:49.668 --> 49:50.702
Let go of me.

49:52.471 --> 49:54.239
You're dead. Let go!

49:59.011 --> 50:00.479
That dumb bastard.

50:12.591 --> 50:14.259
Why are you running away?

50:15.093 --> 50:17.229
- Let go.
- You're dead.

50:57.569 --> 50:59.104
(Copying)

51:07.079 --> 51:08.480
(Complete)

52:38.170 --> 52:40.172
She's definitely hiding something.

52:41.006 --> 52:43.108
Please listen to me and call the police.

52:45.410 --> 52:46.745
That woman should be...

52:47.479 --> 52:50.282
rotting in a psychiatric hospital
or prison, not in this house.

53:11.570 --> 53:13.038
Wait a second.

53:34.660 --> 53:37.196
After locking me up in this backwater,

53:37.196 --> 53:38.397
aren't you even sorry?

53:38.764 --> 53:40.599
I've spent way more time
with Ham Myo Jin...

53:40.599 --> 53:43.702
than with the man
who's supposed to be my future husband.

54:25.844 --> 54:30.182
(REVERSE)

54:30.549 --> 54:32.651
Are you sure no one saw anything?

54:32.651 --> 54:34.052
Actually...

54:34.453 --> 54:36.021
Anyway, what are you going to do now?

54:36.021 --> 54:37.956
It's my turn to move now.

54:37.956 --> 54:40.259
People like you and me...

54:40.259 --> 54:41.760
are cruel and shameless.

54:42.027 --> 54:45.063
Do you even intend to treat Ms. Ham?

54:46.465 --> 54:48.167
I'll be the judge of Myo Jin.

54:48.467 --> 54:50.402
Did I kill Hee Su?

54:51.103 --> 54:52.938
Have you forgotten...

54:53.438 --> 54:54.373
that I told you not to cross the line?

54:54.373 --> 54:55.808
I'm going to kill...

54:55.808 --> 54:57.009
every last one of them.

54:58.210 --> 55:00.212
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
